oc:kn_0849c8d5 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When troubleshooting plugin command execution failures" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT is not expanding: ensure command is loaded from plugin (not standalone), check bash execution is allowed, verify exact syntax ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}. If file not found: verify file exists in plugin directory and path is correct relative to plugin root." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The most common plugin command failures stem from path resolution and environment variable issues" .

oc:kn_3d9473b1 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing plugin command architecture" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Keep commands focused on one clear purpose. Delegate complex logic to scripts. Use agents for multi-step workflows. Use namespaces when plugin has 5+ commands." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Focused commands are easier to maintain, test, and compose into larger workflows" .

oc:kn_3efeb003 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When organizing plugin commands" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Commands placed in plugin-name/commands/ are auto-discovered at plugin load time. No manual registration is required. Commands appear in /help with '(plugin:plugin-name)' label. Subdirectories create namespaces shown as '(plugin:plugin-name:namespace)'." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Auto-discovery eliminates registration boilerplate and ensures commands are available immediately" .

oc:kn_4bb9b192 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building plugin commands that accept arguments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Validate inputs early — check required arguments, verify file existence, and validate argument formats before processing. Use bash grep/test, inline validation in prompts, or script-based validation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Early validation prevents cryptic errors downstream and provides helpful error messages to users" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_5f5b4ac1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any plugin command that references plugin files" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} for all plugin-internal paths — scripts, templates, configuration, and resources. Never use relative paths like ./templates/foo.md as they resolve to the current working directory, not the plugin root." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Relative paths break portability across different installations and working directories" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_bff3843e a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When naming plugin commands" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid generic command names like /test, /run, /do-stuff that conflict with common names. Use descriptive, action-oriented names with hyphens. Consider prefixing with plugin name for uniqueness." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Generic names cause conflicts with built-in or other plugin commands, confusing users" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e0706a00 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building complex plugin commands" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Commands can integrate with multiple plugin components: invoke agents via Task tool, reference skills by name for specialized knowledge, coordinate with hooks that execute on events, and use templates for standardized output." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Leveraging all plugin components creates cohesive, powerful command workflows" .

